stopmodreposts.gui.information.information=\u00A7l\u00A76Have you downloaded all your mods from Curse(-forge), the MinecraftForum or Modrinth? No?\u00A7r\n\nWell, then you might have a problem, lots of other sites re-host mods, without any permissions. And some of them, also include malware into these files.\n \nIn order to be safe from such risks in the future, only download mods from Curse(-forge), the Minecraft Forums or Modrinth.\nPress the button on the left if you wanna know more about this, and be safe in the future.
stopmodreposts.gui.information.information2=\u00A7l\u00A76How can you be sure that the mods you are using now are safe?\u00A7r\n\nIf you have downloaded mods from places other than CurseForge, Curse, the Minecraft Forums or Modrinth, you may be at risk of getting viruses. There are many websites that let you download Minecraft mods, and a lot of them are unsafe. Many websites host mods without their creators' approval - these are often outdated or buggy, and can sometimes come bundled with dangerous malware.\n\nTo avoid getting viruses and malware, and to support mod authors, make sure you only ever download mods from CurseForge, Curse, the Minecraft Forums and Modrinth.
